<item>
            <title>[LU-19536] fault_in_iov_iter_readable() with a spinlock held</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19536</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13805&quot; title=&quot;i/o path: Unaligned direct i/o&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-13805&quot;&gt;LU-13805&lt;/a&gt; and  &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18006&quot; title=&quot;sanity test_119f: crash in ll_dio_user_copy&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-18006&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-18006&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; the following code was introduced:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
       &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rw == WRITE) {
               spin_lock(&amp;amp;sdio-&amp;gt;csd_lock);
...
       &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* fault in the entire userspace iovec */&lt;/span&gt;
       &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (rw == WRITE) {
               &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (unlikely(ll_iov_iter_fault_in_readable(iter, count)))
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think it&apos;s a bad idea to repopulate userspace pages holding a spinlock - this can involve page allocation and I/O.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
